PrecisAuthority: (a) for the sale to the NEWFOUNDLAND TELEPHONE COMPANY LIMITED of a surplus real property situate at the corner of Churchill Avenue and March Drive, in the City of St. John's, Newfoundland, which consists of some 1,212 square metres of land together with the building and equipment known as the Telephone Exchange; and (b) to issue a Licence of Occupation which will allow the licensee to use other off-street installations in connection with the operation of telephone services, for a term of twenty (20) years.
